49:05.720 --> 49:06.881
I got you!

49:18.000 --> 49:19.001
Hey!

49:19.080 --> 49:20.127
No!

49:20.200 --> 49:21.531
Howie!

49:21.600 --> 49:22.601
No, no, no!

49:22.680 --> 49:25.570
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

49:39.680 --> 49:43.207
Honey? Are you okay?
Are you hurt? Hon?

49:46.320 --> 49:48.084
What unholy thing was that?

49:50.640 --> 49:52.404
Howard. Howard.

49:55.160 --> 49:56.286
It's my fault.
No.

49:56.360 --> 49:58.124
I fell asleep.

49:58.640 --> 50:00.881
And they got our boy.
It's all my fault.

50:11.720 --> 50:13.290
Tom, what's she saying?

50:14.120 --> 50:16.327
This is
all of our fault?

50:16.880 --> 50:18.928
He's come
for us all?

50:19.960 --> 50:21.644
He? Who?

50:21.720 --> 50:23.484
Who's he? I don't know.

50:23.560 --> 50:25.244
Mom, what are you
talking about?

50:25.320 --> 50:27.163
Please. Listen.

50:27.480 --> 50:29.721
English. I knew it.

50:30.640 --> 50:32.483
I must tell you something.

50:33.000 --> 50:34.764
To all of you.

50:37.200 --> 50:40.488
It started with the wind.

50:44.280 --> 50:48.126
<i>On a cold winter night,
much like this.</i>

50:49.720 --> 50:52.291
<i>It was almost Christmas.</i>

50:53.320 --> 50:58.201
<i>But this Christmas was darker.
Less cheerful.</i>

51:01.280 --> 51:04.170
<i>But I still
believed in Santa.</i>

51:05.600 --> 51:07.170
<i>In magic,</i>

51:07.960 --> 51:09.962
<i>and miracles.</i>

51:10.880 --> 51:14.851
<i>And the hope that we
could find joy again.</i>

51:16.680 --> 51:18.921
<i>But our village had given up.</i>

51:19.440 --> 51:22.250
<i>On miracles, and on each other.</i>

51:25.880 --> 51:28.531
<i>They had forgotten
the spirit of Christmas.</i>

51:29.320 --> 51:31.891
<i>The sacrifice of giving.</i>

51:34.240 --> 51:37.801
<i>And my family
was no different.</i>

51:41.480 --> 51:45.530
<i>I tried to help them
to believe again,</i>

51:45.640 --> 51:49.611
<i>but we were no longer
the loving family I remembered.</i>

51:53.160 --> 51:55.731
<i>They, too, had given up.</i>

51:57.280 --> 51:59.601
<i>And eventually, so did I.</i>

52:03.520 --> 52:08.287
<i>And for the first time,
I didn't wish for a miracle.</i>

52:09.680 --> 52:12.763
<i>I wished for them
to go away.</i>

52:14.120 --> 52:17.727
<i>A wish I would come to regret.</i>

52:20.360 --> 52:22.283
<i>And that night,</i>

52:22.360 --> 52:25.887
<i>in the darkness of
a howling blizzard,</i>

52:25.960 --> 52:28.531
<i>I got my wish.</i>

52:32.720 --> 52:37.647
<i>I knew Saint Nicholas
was not coming this year.</i>

52:40.520 --> 52:46.801
<i>Instead, it was a much darker,
more ancient spirit.</i>

52:50.120 --> 52:52.885
<i>The shadow of
Saint Nicholas.</i>

52:53.600 --> 52:56.001
<i>It was Krampus.</i>

52:58.120 --> 53:01.408
<i>And as he had for
thousands of years,</i>

53:02.400 --> 53:05.927
<i>Krampus came not to reward,
but to punish.</i>

53:06.720 --> 53:11.009
<i>Not to give, but to take.</i>

53:12.600 --> 53:15.046
<i>He and his helpers.</i>

53:18.720 --> 53:23.726
<i>I could only listen as they dragged
my family into the underworld,</i>

53:23.800 --> 53:27.805
<i>knowing that I would be next.</i>

53:29.360 --> 53:32.807
<i>But Krampus didn't
take me that night.</i>

53:35.480 --> 53:42.443
<i>He left me as a reminder
of what happens when hope is lost,</i>

53:42.520 --> 53:45.808
<i>when belief is forgotten,</i>

53:45.920 --> 53:48.810
<i>and the Christmas spirit dies.</i>

54:05.320 --> 54:07.163
And here I thought
I was the one losing it.

54:07.240 --> 54:09.527
Howard.
What?

54:09.680 --> 54:12.286
You believe this senile horseshit?
I don't know.

54:12.560 --> 54:15.291
